The paper deals with the design of space-time block codes (STBCs) for maximum likelihood (ML) and linear minimum mean squared error (MMSE) reception. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, which deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algebraic structures such as crossed product algebras and cyclic division algebras, which are often used in coding theory and signal processing. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
